      <section class="- topic/section " xtrf="file:/Users/gpage/Documents/Content/ncs_content/9780130210100/topics/english/M01_topic_2_2_5.xml" xtrc="section:2;34:16">
         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Users/gpage/Documents/Content/ncs_content/9780130210100/topics/english/M01_topic_2_2_5.xml" xtrc="p:11;35:13">All states require plumbers to be licensed. Many states require completion of an apprenticeship program and/or <term keyref="M01_trade_definitions/on-the-job_learning_ojl" class="- topic/term " xtrf="file:/Users/gpage/Documents/Content/ncs_content/9780130210100/topics/english/M01_topic_2_2_5.xml" xtrc="term:2;35:185" href="M01_topic_4_4_1.xml#M01_topic_4_4_1/on-the-job_learning_ojl" type="dlentry"><?ditaot usertext?>on-the-job learning (OJL)</term>, or field experience, before testing for a license. When you apply for a license (<xref href="#M01_topic_2_2_5/M01_02101-18_TG-figure2" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/Users/gpage/Documents/Content/ncs_content/9780130210100/topics/english/M01_topic_2_2_5.xml" xtrc="xref:1;35:354" type="fig"><?ditaot usertext?>Figure 2</xref>), you will be tested on your knowledge of both your profession and the local plumbing ordinances.</p>
      </section>
